highcharter

Highcharter es un librera de R para las funciones y grficos highcharts. Highcharter es una biblioteca de visualizacin interactiva en JavaScript. Al igual que su predecesor (?), Highcharter presenta una potente API en lo que a la visualizacin de la data respecta.

Highcharter facilita la creacin de grficos dinmicos. Utiliza una sola funcin, hchart () o highchart(), para dibujar grficos para todo tipo de clases de objetos R: desde el marco de datos hasta el dendrograma. Tambin brinda a los codificadores R una forma prctica de acceder a los otros tipos de grficos populares de Highcharts, Highstock (para grficos financieros) y Highmaps (para mapas esquemticos en proyectos basados en la web), entre otros.

El paquete tiene temas fciles de personalizar, junto con temas integrados como economista, tiempos financieros y otros

Podemos hacer tan argumentativo y flexible nuestro grfico en highcharter a partir de sus argumentos y funciones:

https://www.rdocumentation.org/packages/highcharter/versions/0.8.2

Veamos algunos ejemplos

Columnas

mpgman2 <- mpg %>%
  count(class, year) %>%
  glimpse()
## Rows: 14
## Columns: 3
## $ class <chr> "2seater", "2seater", "compact", "compact", "midsize", "midsi...
## $ year  <int> 1999, 2008, 1999, 2008, 1999, 2008, 1999, 2008, 1999, 2008, 1...
## $ n     <int> 2, 3, 25, 22, 20, 21, 6, 5, 16, 17, 19, 16, 29, 33
hchart(mpgman2, "column", hcaes(x = class, y = n, group = year)) %>% hc_add_theme(hc_theme_darkunica())
hchart(mpgman2, "bar", hcaes(x = class, y = n, group = year))  %>% hc_add_theme(hc_theme_gridlight())

Pastel

hchart(mpgman2 %>% filter(year==2008) , 
       "pie",
       hcaes(x = class, y = n)) %>% 
       hc_add_theme(hc_theme_538())

Dispersin

data(diamonds, mpg, package = "ggplot2")

hchart(mpg, "scatter", hcaes(x = displ, y = hwy, group = class)) %>%
  hc_title(text = "Dispersin diamonds") %>%
  hc_add_theme(hc_theme_economist())

Histograma - densidad

x <- c(rnorm(10000), rnorm(1000, 4, 0.5))

hchart(x, name = "data") 
hchart(diamonds$price) %>% hc_add_theme(hc_theme_elementary())
hchart(density(diamonds$price), type = "area", color = "#B71C1C", name = "Price") %>% hc_add_theme(hc_theme_elementary())

Boxplot

data(diamonds, package = "ggplot2")

hcboxplot(x = diamonds$x, var = diamonds$color,
          name = "Length", color = "#2980b9") %>%
  hc_add_theme(hc_theme_economist())

Treemap

mpgman3 <- mpg %>% 
  group_by(manufacturer) %>% 
  summarise(n = n(), unique = length(unique(model))) %>% 
  arrange(-n, -unique) %>% 
  glimpse()
## `summarise()` ungrouping output (override with `.groups` argument)
## Rows: 15
## Columns: 3
## $ manufacturer <chr> "dodge", "toyota", "volkswagen", "ford", "chevrolet", ...
## $ n            <int> 37, 34, 27, 25, 19, 18, 14, 14, 13, 9, 8, 5, 4, 4, 3
## $ unique       <int> 4, 6, 4, 4, 4, 3, 2, 2, 3, 1, 1, 1, 1, 1, 1
hchart(mpgman3, "treemap", hcaes(x = manufacturer, value = n, color = unique))

Mapa

mapdata <- get_data_from_map(download_map_data("countries/us/us-all"))

set.seed(1234)

data_fake <- mapdata %>% 
  select(code = `hc-a2`) %>% 
  mutate(value = 1e5 * abs(rt(nrow(.), df = 10)))
hcmap("countries/us/us-all", data = data_fake, value = "value",
      joinBy = c("hc-a2", "code"), name = "Fake data",
      dataLabels = list(enabled = TRUE, format = '{point.name}'),
      borderColor = "#0EAD82", borderWidth = 0.1,
      tooltip = list(valueDecimals = 2, valuePrefix = "$", valueSuffix = " USD"))
